<task id="017" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P1.C1 ŌĆö Inventory missing fake config values from baseline logs (READ-ONLY)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>45 min - 1.5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-1, factory-ext, bff-api, testing, p1-c, inventory</tags>
    <parallel-group>1-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Read-only against baseline/ logs; writes only to notes/spikes/factory-config-gaps.md; disjoint from all sibling Wave 1-A tasks (010, 011, 012, 013, 015, 020, 021, 022, 024)</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Inventory the missing fake config values that cause `WebApplicationFactory&lt;Program&gt;` startup
    failures in the baseline test run. Parse the Phase 0 baseline TRX + test output logs for
    `OptionsValidationException` / `InvalidOperationException` / config-bind failures. Produce
    a structured gap list that task 018 (factory extension) consumes.

    This task is READ-ONLY against `baseline/` artifacts. It does NOT touch the factory and does
    NOT touch any production code. Its only output is `notes/spikes/factory-config-gaps.md`.

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-07: factory edits (task 018) run in isolation. This task is the
    SAFE prep step that gathers the input data without touching the factory itself.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent extracting structured config gaps from test failure logs.</role>

  <goal>
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/notes/spikes/factory-config-gaps.md` exists with
    a structured list of missing config keys, suggested fake values, and affected test counts.
    Task 018 consumes this directly.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline-trx">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx</file>
    <file purpose="factory">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/CustomWebAppFactory.cs</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No production code modifications</constraint>
    <constraint source="┬¦4.5">Task 017 is INVENTORY ONLY ŌĆö MUST NOT edit `CustomWebAppFactory.cs`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-07">This task is part of the factory-edit anti-parallelism guard sequence; it runs SAFE (no factory write) and lets task 018 execute in isolation</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/CustomWebAppFactory.cs</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md ┬¦3.4 the WebApplicationFactory startup cluster is ~50-100 tests (one of the
      three largest failure clusters). Root cause: `Program.cs` runs `Options&lt;T&gt;.ValidateDataAnnotations`
      / `ValidateOnStart` which require config values the test factory does not provide. This
      task extracts the exact list from baseline failure traces; task 018 then adds those values
      as additive dictionary entries to the factory (no restructuring per ┬¦4.5).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="001" status="not-started">Baseline TRX + test output captured</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/notes/spikes/factory-config-gaps.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/test-baseline-2026-MM-DD.trx`. Parse stack traces for `OptionsValidationException`, `Microsoft.Extensions.Options`, `Bind`, `Get`, or `Required` failures.</step>
    <step order="2">For each unique stack trace pattern, identify the options type (e.g., `EmailProcessingOptions`, `OpenAiOptions`, `WorkspaceOptions`) and the failing property/key.</step>
    <step order="3">Cross-reference against current `CustomWebAppFactory.cs` (171 LOC) to confirm which keys ARE already provided. Only keys NOT in the factory's existing dictionary are gaps.</step>
    <step order="4">For each gap, propose a fake value: empty-string for strings, `00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000` for guids, `https://localhost.test/fake` for URLs, etc. Default to "least-functional valid value" so test paths aren't accidentally exercised.</step>
    <step order="5">Count affected tests per gap (best-effort grep over baseline TRX for failures referencing that options type).</step>
    <step order="6">Write `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/notes/spikes/factory-config-gaps.md` with sections:
      - (a) `## Inventory summary` ŌĆö gap count, estimated affected test count
      - (b) `## Per-gap detail` ŌĆö table with columns: Options type | Missing key | Proposed fake value | Affected test count | Source TRX line(s)
      - (c) `## Inputs for task 018` ŌĆö bulleted plain-English instructions on what to add to factory's existing config dictionary
      - (d) `## Hosted services to remove` ŌĆö any `IHostedService` that crashes on startup in tests and should be `RemoveAll`'d</step>
    <step order="7">Update `current-task.md` declaring P1.C1 prep complete; task 018 ready to run in isolation.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify `git status` shows changes ONLY under `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/notes/` ŌĆö NOT under `tests/`, NOT under `src/`, etc.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/notes/spikes/factory-config-gaps.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`notes/spikes/factory-config-gaps.md` exists with the 4 named sections</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-gap detail table has at least 1 row (factory IS missing config per design.md ┬¦3.4)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No modifications to `tests/`, `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`CustomWebAppFactory.cs` NOT modified (NFR-07 prep step)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
